01:11:52.318 --> 01:12:13.927
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:12:13.927 --> 01:12:28.440
What can make me whole again?

01:12:28.440 --> 01:12:41.675
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:12:41.675 --> 01:13:06.159
Oh, precious is the flow that makes me white as snow.

01:13:56.640 --> 01:13:57.1000
No other fountain I know, nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:13:57.1000 --> 01:14:10.480
What can wash away my sin?

01:14:10.480 --> 01:14:13.738
Yeah, I said it right.

01:14:13.738 --> 01:14:16.186
Nothing but the blood of Jesus.

01:14:16.186 --> 01:14:21.093
What can make me whole again?

01:14:21.093 --> 01:14:27.097
What are you doing, baby?

01:14:27.097 --> 01:14:29.554
You're fine.

01:14:39.314 --> 01:14:39.577
I just need you to pull with me.

01:14:39.577 --> 01:14:40.340
I'm praying.

01:15:46.751 --> 01:15:47.455
I don't know where you want me.

01:15:52.320 --> 01:15:52.570
You're fine right there.

01:15:54.853 --> 01:15:55.386
I know you didn't want to come on.

01:15:55.386 --> 01:15:56.719
I get it.

01:16:04.800 --> 01:16:05.400
But the Lord said to pray.

01:16:05.400 --> 01:16:06.600
Hush.

01:16:06.600 --> 01:16:09.253
You're good, love.

01:16:09.253 --> 01:16:11.386
I know you.

01:16:11.386 --> 01:16:15.039
Okay, we're going to get him in 2026.

01:16:15.039 --> 01:16:18.232
We're going to move this thing.

01:16:18.232 --> 01:16:19.503
I'm here.

01:16:19.503 --> 01:16:20.351
Ready?

01:16:20.351 --> 01:16:23.160
Hold my hand.

01:16:23.160 --> 01:16:29.307
Father, I thank you, Lord, for the blood.

01:16:29.307 --> 01:16:33.486
Thank you, Father, for your grace and for your mercy.

01:16:33.486 --> 01:16:36.491
See, now that's an interesting thing.

01:16:36.491 --> 01:16:38.784
We run to that eye.

01:16:38.784 --> 01:16:39.552
We run.

01:16:39.552 --> 01:16:40.320
We run.

01:16:40.320 --> 01:16:46.920
I wait for him to lead, but I can feel that vein of prayer.

01:16:46.920 --> 01:16:49.964
And I saw a massive eye.

01:16:49.964 --> 01:16:57.880
And when I went up to that right there, I saw a massive face.

01:17:14.183 --> 01:17:14.731
And I was on a path.

01:17:14.731 --> 01:17:16.949
There was a path that was winding.

01:17:16.949 --> 01:17:25.680
And the face was set before me, but all I saw was the eye.

01:17:25.680 --> 01:17:28.440
And I believe that was the Father right then.

01:17:28.440 --> 01:17:30.053
Like you could see an eye.

01:17:30.053 --> 01:17:31.599
It was a massive eye looking.

01:17:42.719 --> 01:17:43.110
And they're watching you as you're on this path.

01:17:49.910 --> 01:17:58.159
And I could see the path that was winding and it was a beautiful white road, and all on the sides there was no way.

01:17:58.159 --> 01:18:07.576
It was just straight down on both sides, but the path was elevated and it was going straight to the eye.

01:18:14.560 --> 01:18:15.120
And I don't know what that means, but that's what I was seeing right then.

01:18:15.120 --> 01:18:23.451
And instantaneously I feel—I'd say I'm trying to correct anything I've done.

01:18:23.451 --> 01:18:26.280
I'm not trying to pick at anybody.

01:18:26.280 --> 01:18:28.500
Instantaneously, I see the Holy Ghost.

01:18:28.500 --> 01:18:30.850
I say, 'Oh, forgive me Lord.

01:18:30.850 --> 01:18:35.422
If I have done anything wrong to anybody, forgive me.

01:18:35.422 --> 01:18:39.430
My heart is always to remain pure before the Father.

01:18:39.430 --> 01:18:53.780
' And the word of the Lord came to us and said, 'Not everybody is going to like you, but they'll like your fruit, the fruit of your ministry.

01:18:53.780 --> 01:19:01.199
' But my personality type is very hard to deal with a lot.

01:19:01.199 --> 01:19:25.810
I'm very, very strong in what I believe and what I think because I follow with the Holy Ghost, and when he guides and tells you things, it's not always a popular opinion.

01:19:25.810 --> 01:19:33.627
And I think that that makes my personality type probably even with family.

01:19:47.600 --> 01:19:48.000
I'm pretty rigid.

01:19:52.480 --> 01:19:52.810
Not with you, but I'm talking about with the ones on the outer.

01:19:52.810 --> 01:19:58.670
You're passionate in what you believe, with the Lord.

01:19:58.670 --> 01:20:14.400
But I'm very strong and it probably rubs even pastoral people wrong because of who I am, and I'm not changing because it got me where I'm at with the Holy Ghost.

01:20:14.400 --> 01:20:17.313
He comes and talks to me.

01:20:17.313 --> 01:20:24.389
But I think sometimes I come across gruff and I go, 'Well, you know what?

01:20:24.389 --> 01:20:32.008
God will use what he is why he comes and visits, I guess,' because I don't bend and I don't burn.

01:20:32.008 --> 01:20:38.446
I will say what he tells me to say and there's no compromise in it.

01:20:39.794 --> 01:20:44.020
And I've stood in front of people and he says, 'Sit on the back row.

01:20:44.020 --> 01:20:50.914
Do what I tell you to do.

01:20:50.914 --> 01:20:57.093
' I do exactly what I'm instructed to do everywhere I go.

01:21:04.204 --> 01:21:08.373
And I say, 'This is what he told me to do.

01:21:08.373 --> 01:21:12.578
' And he goes, 'These are assignments.

01:21:12.578 --> 01:21:20.868
' And it happens every single time I go to these places.

01:21:28.400 --> 01:21:28.760
This is what I do all the time.

01:21:38.320 --> 01:21:39.537
It's very interesting.

01:21:49.600 --> 01:21:49.912
But I've always been obedient.

01:21:49.912 --> 01:21:51.783
Now your season's done.

01:21:51.783 --> 01:21:57.146
Your season's this, your season that, and I go exactly what he asked me to do.

01:21:57.146 --> 01:22:02.267
And that's that path I just saw.

01:22:02.267 --> 01:22:05.776
I saw myself walking on that path.

01:22:05.776 --> 01:22:14.640
I saw it, but I saw I was walking to an eye.

01:22:32.400 --> 01:22:32.620
And the eye kind of freaked me out right then, and that's why I paused and I said I got to pray over this massive face.

01:22:32.620 --> 01:22:40.550
I could see the cheekbone, I could see it, and it was looking.

01:22:40.560 --> 01:23:00.453
It was halfway like this and it was looking right at me, and I was walking toward the path.

01:23:00.453 --> 01:23:05.875
Father, I thank you, Lord.

01:23:05.875 --> 01:23:14.719
Open the eyes of my heart, Lord.

01:23:14.719 --> 01:23:19.296
Open the eyes of my heart.

01:23:22.080 --> 01:23:24.656
I want to see you.

01:23:24.656 --> 01:23:33.120
I want to see you.

01:23:33.120 --> 01:23:39.509
Open the eyes of my heart, Lord.

01:23:39.509 --> 01:23:51.515
Open the eyes of my heart.

01:24:08.400 --> 01:24:11.954
I want to see you.

01:24:12.171 --> 01:24:17.600
To see you high and lifted up, shining in the light of your glory.

01:24:17.600 --> 01:24:30.740
Pour out your power and love as we sing, 'Holy, holy, holy.

01:24:30.740 --> 01:24:39.520
' High and lifted up, shining in the light of your glory.

01:24:39.520 --> 01:25:00.933
Pour out your power and love as we sing, 'Holy, holy, holy.

01:25:00.933 --> 01:25:25.438
' High and lifted up, shining in the light of your glory.

01:25:25.438 --> 01:26:30.839
Pour out your power and love as we sing, 'Holy, holy, holy.

01:26:30.839 --> 01:26:32.906
' I want to see you.

01:26:32.906 --> 01:26:35.520
I want to see you.

01:26:35.520 --> 01:26:43.289
Oh Father, we worship you.

01:26:43.289 --> 01:26:47.800
How small we are, how small we are compared to how big you are.

01:26:47.800 --> 01:26:56.160
How small we truly are on that path.

01:26:56.160 --> 01:27:01.800
How big you truly are, Father.

01:27:01.800 --> 01:27:05.679
For you are great.

01:27:05.679 --> 01:27:10.320
Your eye is great.

01:27:10.320 --> 01:27:20.468
Father, this is such a winding road.

01:27:20.468 --> 01:27:24.960
Every one of us is on this path.

01:27:24.960 --> 01:27:30.124
Every one of us is on the path where we seek you.

01:27:30.124 --> 01:27:33.303
Every one of us is seeking your eyes.

01:27:33.303 --> 01:27:35.131
We're seeking your face.

01:27:35.131 --> 01:27:52.353
We're seeking you, and your eyes are on us.

01:28:00.000 --> 01:28:04.560
For his eye is on the sparrow, and I know he watches over me.

01:28:04.560 --> 01:28:06.427
I believe this.

01:28:06.427 --> 01:28:13.440
Let not your heart be troubled.

01:28:13.440 --> 01:28:17.787
Why should the shadow fall?

01:28:17.787 --> 01:28:21.822
I'm resting on your goodness and Jesus is my portion.

01:28:21.822 --> 01:28:26.307
My constant friend is he, for his eye is on the sparrow.

01:28:33.759 --> 01:28:34.319
And I know that he watches over me.

01:28:41.680 --> 01:28:49.280
And I sing because I'm happy and I sing because I'm free, for his eye is on the sparrow and I know he watches over me.

01:28:49.280 --> 01:28:55.813
Thank you, Father, that you are watching over us, for that eye is on the sparrow.

01:29:11.280 --> 01:29:11.947
And I sing because I'm happy and I sing because I'm free.

01:29:11.947 --> 01:29:23.440
Oh, his eye is on the sparrow and I know he watches over me.

01:29:50.994 --> 01:29:51.245
And I sing because I'm happy and I sing because I'm free.

01:29:51.245 --> 01:29:58.427
Oh, his eye is on the sparrow and I know he watches over me.

01:29:58.427 --> 01:30:01.568
Thank you, Lord, for the eye.

01:30:01.568 --> 01:30:07.749
His eye is watching over us as he's on that path.

01:30:19.490 --> 01:30:19.860
That's the song that came to me.

01:30:29.920 --> 01:30:33.303
I just thank him for the eye.

01:30:55.813 --> 01:30:56.000
Even as hard as weeks go, his eye is on the sparrow.

01:30:56.000 --> 01:30:56.560
His eye is watching over me.

01:30:56.711 --> 01:31:05.937
I don't know all the words to it, but Father, I thank you, Lord, for your hand on us.

01:31:28.800 --> 01:31:29.138
Oh Father, we worship you.

01:31:29.138 --> 01:31:37.848
Let not your heart be troubled because Jesus is my portion; my constant friend is he.

01:31:37.848 --> 01:31:47.710
Thank you that you're my portion.

01:31:47.710 --> 01:33:25.836
Because we walk through that garden alone, my Father, when the dew is still on the roses, and he walks with me and he talks with me and he tells me I am his own.

01:35:02.539 --> 01:35:02.919
And the joy we'll share as we tarry there, none other has ever known.

01:35:02.919 --> 01:35:04.919
We worship you, Father.

01:35:04.919 --> 01:35:09.589
We get the vein of where you want us to pray today.

01:35:09.939 --> 01:35:11.887
And we're not in a hurry.

01:35:16.518 --> 01:35:17.675
I have nowhere else to be.

01:35:17.675 --> 01:35:21.257
I follow after you, Father.

01:35:21.257 --> 01:35:31.195
I thank you, Lord, that I find you and you find me.

01:35:31.195 --> 01:35:40.016
We're in the midst of that garden alone where the dew is still on the roses, Father.

01:35:52.356 --> 01:35:52.631
Oh Father, we thank you.

01:36:03.394 --> 01:36:03.703
And the voice I hear as we tarry there, I worship you, for you are good and your mercy endures forever.

01:36:14.104 --> 01:36:14.416
I wait for that.

01:36:14.416 --> 01:36:17.190
Oh Father, we worship you.

01:36:17.190 --> 01:36:20.960
Blessed are you, Father.

01:36:20.960 --> 01:36:22.940
Great is thy faithfulness.

01:36:22.940 --> 01:36:28.400
Morning by morning, new mercies I see.

01:36:28.400 --> 01:36:33.600
All I have needed, thy hands have provided.

01:36:33.600 --> 01:36:36.053
Great is thy faithfulness, Lord, unto me.

01:36:36.053 --> 01:36:47.279
Thank you, Lord, for your faithfulness to us.

01:36:47.279 --> 01:36:53.600
All I have needed, thy hands have provided.

01:36:53.600 --> 01:36:56.719
Morning by morning, new mercies I see.

01:36:56.719 --> 01:37:05.760
I thank you, Father, that you've been so faithful to us.

01:37:24.880 --> 01:37:25.160
I thank you that you've been faithful this year to us as we close out 2025 soon.

01:37:27.560 --> 01:37:28.080
You have been so good to us, Master.

01:37:28.080 --> 01:37:30.880
We have air in our lungs.

01:37:30.880 --> 01:37:33.960
We have our hearts beating.

01:37:33.960 --> 01:37:39.580
We have all that you have given us, Father.

01:37:40.686 --> 01:37:42.333
And we're so grateful for every person here.

01:37:42.333 --> 01:37:49.150
We're grateful, Father, for all that you've done to draw us near.

01:37:49.150 --> 01:37:52.520
We're so grateful for your coming on this earth.

01:37:52.520 --> 01:37:56.194
We're so grateful for your birth.

01:37:56.194 --> 01:38:05.920
Thank you, Father, that you came here as a beautiful Savior for the world.

01:38:05.920 --> 01:38:09.519
Great is thy faithfulness, morning by morning.

01:38:09.519 --> 01:38:10.320
Thank you, Lord.

01:38:10.320 --> 01:38:17.239
O holy night, the stars are brightly shining.

01:38:17.239 --> 01:38:23.590
It is the night of our dear Savior's birth.

01:38:23.600 --> 01:38:46.504
Long lay the world in sin and error pining till he appeared and the soul felt its worth.

01:38:48.680 --> 01:38:59.120
A thrill of hope, the weary world rejoices, for yonder breaks a new and glorious morn.

01:38:59.120 --> 01:39:01.246
Fall on your knees!

01:39:01.246 --> 01:39:03.547
Oh, hear the angel voices!

01:39:03.547 --> 01:39:09.789
Oh night divine, oh night when Christ was born.

01:39:19.875 --> 01:39:20.426
I don't know all the words.

01:39:27.760 --> 01:39:28.470
You did it.

01:39:28.480 --> 01:39:47.520
But it's beautiful.

01:39:51.280 --> 01:39:51.520
I love it.

01:40:05.040 --> 01:40:05.280
It's for him anyway.

01:40:05.280 --> 01:40:06.719
It's not for them.

01:40:06.719 --> 01:40:08.408
I feel him.

01:40:08.408 --> 01:40:25.240
So many people, when you have an auditorium of almost 7,000 people watching you, but I lose myself in him and you're just a part of it.

01:40:29.653 --> 01:40:29.902
I honest to goodness could care less if you're here.

01:40:29.902 --> 01:40:31.093
I seek him.

01:40:31.093 --> 01:40:33.851
I get the words because I want him.

01:40:33.851 --> 01:40:36.880
I want it to please him.

01:40:36.880 --> 01:40:42.159
I know that he loves a cheerful noise; he inhabits the praises of his people.

01:40:42.159 --> 01:40:45.484
But when you seek him, you'll find him.

01:40:46.907 --> 01:41:02.360
And when his presence fills my house the way it does when I sing to him, there's nothing that compares to it.

01:41:05.333 --> 01:41:09.406
It changes things so that even people, when they come over, they don't want to leave.

01:41:09.406 --> 01:41:13.969
They don't even know why they're wanting to stay.

01:41:13.969 --> 01:41:22.571
But it's him, and I want him to always be welcome here, that I always provide an atmosphere in my home of worship.

01:41:22.571 --> 01:41:31.360
Now Paisley's on the kick; she puts Brother Hagin on all the time.

01:41:31.360 --> 01:41:34.160
She says she's taking notes.

01:41:34.160 --> 01:41:43.600
She goes up in her room and she writes notes all the time.

01:41:43.600 --> 01:41:47.280
'This is what Brother Hagin said today.

01:41:47.280 --> 01:41:56.053
' At 10 years old, I'm so proud of you.

01:41:56.053 --> 01:42:00.029
'This is what Brother Hagin said today, Daddy.

01:42:00.029 --> 01:42:48.477
' The thrill of hope, the weary world rejoices for yonder breaks a new and glorious morning.

01:42:48.477 --> 01:42:57.678
Fall on your knees!

01:42:57.678 --> 01:43:50.310
Oh, hear the angel voices!

01:43:50.320 --> 01:44:57.531
Oh night divine, oh night when Christ was born.

01:44:57.531 --> 01:45:14.859
Oh Father, I think the atmosphere is good now.

01:47:05.782 --> 01:47:06.365
It's like I have to feel the thermostat to get in that prayer zone.

01:47:06.365 --> 01:47:09.280
And I wait.

01:47:09.280 --> 01:47:51.600
Oh Father, what's on your heart today?

01:48:15.660 --> 01:48:16.050
A thrill of hope.

01:48:16.050 --> 01:48:18.709
You're my thrill of hope.

01:48:44.658 --> 01:48:45.013
The weary world, Lord, it rejoices.

01:48:45.013 --> 01:49:04.919
There are so many weary, Father.

01:49:04.919 --> 01:49:34.959
There are so many people that are down and out and downtrodden.

01:49:59.159 --> 01:49:59.599
They're so upset.

01:49:59.599 --> 01:50:02.457
Their finances are bad.

01:50:10.920 --> 01:50:11.200
They tell us, 'Oh, we're having a hard time.

01:50:11.200 --> 01:50:14.697
' They say, 'My job is so bad.

01:50:14.697 --> 01:50:16.593
My wife is bad.

01:50:16.593 --> 01:50:18.365
My husband's bad.

01:50:18.365 --> 01:50:32.240
' But Father, I know that if they could just have that one moment with you, they could get that fresh touch from the Master's hand.

01:50:32.240 --> 01:50:49.919
So many people search for drugs, sex, or money; they're looking in all the wrong places and all they have to do is go vertical and they find you.

01:51:03.486 --> 01:51:03.931
All this other stuff—popularity, fame, fortune—it's so pathetic.

01:51:03.931 --> 01:51:05.268
Only Jesus.

01:51:05.268 --> 01:51:11.512
You fill our cup, Lord, we lift it up.

01:51:11.512 --> 01:51:18.537
Lord, come and quench this thirsting of our soul.

01:51:18.537 --> 01:51:29.406
Bread of heaven, feed me till I want no more.

01:51:29.406 --> 01:51:47.430
Fill my cup, fill it up and make me whole.

01:51:47.440 --> 01:51:51.554
Father, I thank you that you make us whole.

01:51:51.554 --> 01:51:57.867
Oh Lord, we worship you.

01:51:57.867 --> 01:51:59.980
You are welcome in this place.

01:51:59.980 --> 01:52:03.440
Holy Spirit, you are welcome here in this place.

01:52:03.440 --> 01:52:09.200
Omnipotent Father of mercy and grace, thou art welcome in this place.

01:52:09.200 --> 01:52:14.880
Holy Spirit, you are welcome in this place.

01:52:14.880 --> 01:52:36.790
Omnipotent Father of mercy and grace, thou art welcome in this place.

01:52:57.333 --> 01:52:57.547
For in your presence there's healing divine.

01:52:57.547 --> 01:53:06.000
No other power can heal, Lord, but thine, Holy Spirit.

